@ChrisKing189362 Feel free to say whatever you want, but it doesn’t change the reality of things.

It’s all public information with $IREN management track record with $BKKT and $ASST.

It’s definitely important to know if someone is  making the primary argument of trusting in management to handle dilution

@hoiyeahhhh Across $BKKT, $ASST, and maybe $IREN. The strategy has been identical. 

Generate massive retail hype around a hot narrative (Bitcoin treasuries, AI agents, DCs), wait for the stock to spike, and immediately dump shares via ATMs to fund operations and pay executive SBCs.

The companies themselves are fine but the individual retail shareholder is left hurt the most.
